nbc today show cohost jane pauley planned 
to announce on the air friday morning that shes leaving the show 
ending more than a month of speculation network sources said 
thursday night 
pauley whose job with cohost bryant gumbel will be taken by 
deborah norville will leave at the end of the year and anchor a 
primetime news series some time next year a source close to the 
program said 
norville was made news anchor of the twohour toprated morning 
program on sept 5 norvilles successor as news anchor at the 
earlier nbc news at sunrise has yet to be selected the source 
said 
for pauley 39 the move will end a 13year run of the show that 
began in 1975 when she came here from nbcowned wmaqtv in chicago 
to succeed barbara walters when walter left to join abc news 
pauley was reportedly unhappy about changes that have been made 
on the show including the shift of former today news anchor 
john palmer to norvilles previous job pauley has refused 
previously to comment about her impending move 
she has said however that she would be staying at nbc news 
where her contract still has two years to run 
her plans to leave were confirmed in an interview wednesday with 
today weatherman willard scott 
nbc planned to announce when shed leave last friday a source 
close to the situation said but postponed that when today was 
hurriedly sent to san francisco tuesday night to help cover the 
killer earthquake there 
pauleys reported discontent over changes in the show focused in 
part on the addition of two layers of new management by the end of 
the year 
nbc sports president dick ebersol this summer was given a second 
job as nbc news vice president for today starting next year a 
newly created position of senior executive producer is to be filled 
by david nuell now executive producer of the syndicated 
entertainment tonight series 
the future status of the current today executive producer 
marty ryan is not yet known 
