correspondent and bureau chief for the associated press has been 
named deputy director of aps corporate communications department 
the appointment was announced wednesday by wendell wood collins 
head of the department at aps international headquarters among 
her other responsibilities hooker will edit ap world a magazine 
for the news cooperatives worldwide staff 
hooker 44 was bureau chief in hartford conn for three years 
before resigning last year to study theology her previous 
assignments for the ap included newswoman and news editor in 
hartford correspondent in springfield mass and newswoman and 
news editor in boston 
hooker is from sharon pa and worked for the hartford courant 
before joining the ap in hartford in 1974 she has worked as a copy 
editor for the boston globe during the past year 
