very cautious about selling it hightechnology equipment 
answering questions during a visit to a us air base in eastern 
england cheney said it was necessary to maintain the cocom regime 
the organization of industrial democracies that regulates trade 
in items to soviet bloc nations cocom stands for coordinating 
committee for multilateral export controls 
cheney arrived here wednesday from a nato meeting in portugal 
and had talks with british defense secretary tom king his next 
stop was west germany 
the export committees 17 member states the united states 14 
of its nato allies australia and japan are meeting at a secret 
venue in paris 
cheney welcomed the changes in the soviet union and eastern 
europe but said the west needs to remain very cautious about the 
kinds of technology we allow to be transferred to the eastern 
bloc 
he said the soviet union still has a huge arsenal of 
intercontinental ballistic weapons and other strategic systems 
targeted against the united states and other nato members 
they are the only nation in the world capable of destroying 
us i think it is in our interests under those circumstances to 
continue the cocom regime cheney said 
the united states cocom allies are pressing for an easing of 
trade restrictions leaving washington all but isolated according 
to a us source who spoke on condition of anonymity before the 
meeting began wednesday 
european members accuse the united states of failing to adapt to 
the changes in the east bloc and of using cocom to protect us 
manufacturers from foreign competition 
