<TEXT>
soviet president mikhail s gorbachev 
today announced a major plan to reduce nuclear weapons in the 
baltic sea that will include the scrapping of moscows 
nucleararmed submarines there 
in a goodwill gesture to northern europe the kremlin chief said 
the soviet union has removed all tactical nuclear missiles that 
could strike the region and will take certain types of sealaunched 
nuclear weapons out of the baltic sea 
he made these announcements in remarks prepared for delivery to 
1500 finnish politicians businessmen and other invited guests 
gorbachev said the eventual goal was to rid the baltic of 
nuclear weapons 
we are prepared to come to agreement with all the nuclear 
powers and the baltic states on effective guarantees for the 
nuclearfree status of the baltic sea he said 
gorbachev said the steps were being taken unilaterally and were 
a followup to a speech he gave two years ago in the soviet 
northern port of murmansk many of his proposals in that speech 
including a call for a nuclearfree zone in northern europe were 
dismissed by nato 
in washington white house press secretary marlin fitzwater 
said we do not believe nuclearfree zones contribute to security 
in europe 
most of these proposals have been designed to affect nato 
deterrence capability while leaving soviet nuclear weapons 
intact fitzwater said on the other hand we do appreciate the 
intent of this and if it can develop into something concrete why 
that might be a hopeful sign 
gorbachev said the soviet union already has taken two of its 
golfclass submarines out of operation from the baltic and he 
pledged to destroy the remaining four by the end of next year the 
nuclear missiles aboard the subs will also be destroyed and not 
replaced he said 
gorbachev did not specify which types of sealaunched nuclear 
weapons the soviets would remove from the baltic sea 
