<TEXT>
the chairman of the us civil rights 
commission said thursday he resigned as head of the panel to give 
president bush an opportunity to set the administrations civil 
rights agenda and name a new chairman 
it is time for the new administration which has been too 
reticent to give forth to speak to the question and make clear 
what it has to contribute to the debate on civil rights william 
b allen told a news conference at the national press club 
allen whose tenure at the agency has been marked by 
controversy said he could not speak for the administration because 
i have not had a single conversation with president bush since 
his election last year 
president bush alone can tell the country where he stands and 
what he has to contribute he added 
by naming a new chairman bush could give a particular signal 
of the mark with which he chooses to stamp the agency allen said 
the white house revealed last week that bush had accepted 
allens resignation from the commission asked to comment thursday 
white house press secretary marlin fitzwater said only we accept 
his resignation 
allen had said last march the president would have to ask him 
personally to resign his post after reports that bush had planned 
to replace him with arthur a fletcher a moderate republican and 
one of bushs early black political supporters 
allen distributed copies of the letter of resignation he had 
sent to the white house dated sept 9 
attached was a terse onesentence letter from bush dated oct 
16 saying only i accept your resignation as chairman of the 
united states commission on civil rights effective immediately 
in his letter allen who is black challenged bush to reduce 
civil rights litigation and to turn our country around away from 
its conscious discouragement of american blacks in particular from 
relying upon and profiting from the justice of our courts of law 
allen said bush should work to simplify civil right law which 
now probably stands second only to our tax code for ambiguities 
complexities and internal contradictions 
allens tenure as chairman of the panel has been marked by 
confrontation with other commissioners and public incidents such as 
his arrest at gunpoint when he intervened in a custody battle over 
an indian girl 
allen a professor of government at harvey mudd college in 
claremont calif was appointed chairman of the commission in june 
1988 after the death of clarence pendleton 
allen came under fire from fellow commissioners recently for a 
speech titled blacks animals homosexuals what is a minority 
he delivered earlier this month before a conservative coalition 
in a 61 vote the commission branded the speech thoughtless 
disgusting and unnecessarily inflammatory 
i do not believe in coddling people said allen in defending 
his leadership style 
my predecessor in the office im afraid wore himself out 
holding the hands of his colleagues and trying to patch together a 
consensus which really existed as nothing more than a paper 
consensus 
saying he felt a moral obligation as the only conservative 
on the panel allen said he would continue to serve on the 
commission his sixyear term expires dec 1 1992 
commission vice chairman murray friedman will act as the head of 
the agency until bush appoints a new chairman 
