unreservedly recognizes finlands neutral status 
proposed that the next followup meeting to the 1975 helsinki 
accords which outlined eastwest security measures cooperation in 
economic and scientific and human rights affairs be held in 1992 
in helsinki and be attended by leaders of the 35 states involved 
paved the way for direct contacts between legislators in the 
