the compressor immediately and they were on their way out of the 
building brewster said some were outside and some were just 
inside 
he said there were 15 workers in the gas compressor building 
about onequarter mile from the plants main building in 
southwestern wyoming 
the dead man was struck by one wall of the steel building that 
was blown out by the blast 
it appears as if he had just gotten out the door when the 
explosion occurred brewster said 
brewster said a short fire followed the explosion 
once the explosion occurred the fire was over because the 
supply of gas to the building was cut off as soon as the leak was 
detected he said 
brewster said the plant had a good safety record before 
wednesdays explosion no workers had lost time on the job because 
of an injury in seven years 
</TEXT>
