condition hopefully it will stop at least some of the 
deterioration said wiznia the director of the pediatric aids 
unit at bronxlebanon hospital 
until thursday doctors were not permitted to prescribe azt the 
only governmentapproved antiaids drug for anyone under the age 
of 13 
but health and human services secretary louis sullivan lifted 
the restriction saying preliminary evidence indicated that the 
drug is effective and seems to be safe 
children ages 3 months to 12 years who have symptoms of advanced 
infection with the aids virus will be eligible to receive azt free 
under the program sponsored by the maker burroughs wellcome co it 
was previously only available to children enrolled in clinical 
trials 
almost 1900 children under 13 have aids about 2 percent of all 
aids cases according to the national centers for disease control 
pediatric aids specialists generally welcomed thursdays news 
but cautioned that azt was no more a cureall in children than in 
adults 
research studies that involved more than 200 children have 
indicated that azt may prolong their survival without raising the 
risk of side effects 
anecdotal evidence has been mixed 
dr ayre rubinstein who has worked on pediatric aids for a 
decade at the albert einstein college of medicine in the bronx has 
used azt for some time in symptomatic patients 
one was a 6yearold girl who lost the use of her legs from 
progressive encephalopathy a brain disease he said after 
receiving azt there was a marked improvement 
yet the same treatment had no effect when it was tried on 
another patient 
the same syndrome about the same age he said so you can 
see from that its very hard to predict the outcome of the azt on 
brain disease 
dr ed connor who runs the pediatric azt trials at childrens 
hospital in newark nj said initial evidence indicates that 
the majority overall have benefited 
he mentioned one girl who has been receiving azt by prescription 
because shes over 13 
she was losing weight and really not doing very well in 
school connor said she improved significantly and now 
religiously takes her azt because shes really seen the benefits 
azt also called zidovudine was approved by the food and drug 
administration for teenagers and adults with advanced symptoms of 
aids in march 1987 
doctors thursday praised the new form of azt a 
strawberryflavored syrup that is easier for children to swallow 
than capsules are it also allows dosages to be adjusted for body 
size 
but all warn that there is still much to be learned about the 
drug which is highly toxic and can cause serious side effects such 
as anemia and low white blood cell counts 
studies will continue to evaluate the effects on children of azt 
in combination with other drugs and the benefits of the drug when 
used in children in earlier stages of the disease 
the number of small children treated with azt in this country 
has been so small that i dont think you can make a statement as to 
whether its going to work wiznia said 
rubinstein said he will not use azt as a prophylactic in his 
pediatric clinic the largest in the country until more research 
is done on the proper dosage 
there are some people who say we are ready to take the 
risks its a fatal disease well prescribe it 
i dont think thats the right attitude rubinstein said 
