before your task is complete 
she said there is no difference in our basic economic 
beliefs and britains economy is vastly stronger 
lawson a former financial journalist is a member of parliament 
whose career highlight was his 1988 budget which slashed taxes for 
the top income bracket from 60 percent to 40 percent 
plump and darkly handsome he has a boyish funloving manner 
and is known to have complained that his government salary is too 
low and that he would like to go into business in july he lost 
his official country residence in what was seen as an unseemly 
byproduct of a cabinet reshuffle 
walters a johns hopkins economist is mrs thatchers appointee 
and is sometimes referred to as her economic guru one of the group 
of freemarket apostles who shaped mrs thatchers thinking in the 
1970s 
he was her adviser from 1981 to 1983 went back to johns 
hopkins and returned to a downing street post earlier this year in 
what was seen as a slight to lawson 
on tuesday night lawson publicly rebuked him telling a tv 
interviewer i think it is right that advisers do not talk or 
write in public 
opposition labor party members elated at the apparent disarray 
in conservative party ranks said lawson must have made his 
decision when mrs thatcher failed to use a regular appearance in 
parliament to express absolute confidence in her chancellor 
labor leader neil kinnock said when the prime minister failed 
to give real support to nigel lawson this afternoon he really 
could not stay and it is entirely the prime ministers fault 
mrs thatcher gave the job to major just three months after she 
lifted him out of political obscurity and made him foreign 
secretary at the age of 46 
major is a former senior treasury official born into a 
bluecollar family with a father who was for a time a circus 
trapeze artist he represents the new breed of workingclass 
tories who have flourished in the thatcher decade 
major inherits an economy suffering from inflation of 76 
