a federal jury convicted three men and 
acquitted two others thursday on charges they conspired with 
colombian drug kingpin carlos lehder rivas to smuggle cocaine into 
the united states 
the jury reached its verdict after 18 hours of deliberation over 
three days in the socalled son of lehder trial which grew out 
of testimony in last years trial of lehder lehder 40 reputedly 
one of the founders of the medellin cocaine cartel was convicted 
and is serving a life prison term 
the five defendants in the sevenweeklong trial were accused of 
conspiring with lehder to either smuggle cocaine into the united 
states or distribute it once it got there 
jack carlton reed 59 was found guilty of conspiracy to 
distribute cocaine and operating a continuing criminal enterprise 
reed was convicted last year on drug conspiracy charges and 
sentenced to 15 years in prison 
prosecutors called reed one of lehders chief lieutenants who 
worked as lehders contact with americans in the organization 
hyannis mass attorney barry kane 52 and donald lady 41 of 
pomona calif were both convicted of conspiracy to import 
cocaine but were found innocent of conspiracy to distribute 
cocaine 
kane collapsed after us district judge john h moore ii 
formally pronounced him guilty but was quickly revived 
reed kane and lady face prison sentences of 10 years to life 
moore ordered them held pending sentencing jan 12 
according to the charges kane picked up 250 kilograms of 
cocaine from cartel leader pablo escobars ranch and flew it back 
to the us on two occasions in the summer of 1977 
lady was accused of acquiring a ranch in the baja peninsula to 
be used as a waystation for cocaine flights from colombia in early 
1987 
