i880 doubledecker to collapse 
first of all i want to say that i believe there will be 
surprises there will be lessons to learn from this collapse the 
obvious thing is that the columns failed said buckle who was 
among the first experts to spend extensive time at the site the 
question is did they fail first or was it something else he 
said 
other factors he said could range from a theory advanced 
wednesday by berkeley scientists that the base of the upperdeck 
columns failed first to a theory of unstable ground beneath and a 
lack of uniform rigidity along the length of the structure we 
have learned from the past that variations in rigidity can cause 
problems in earthquakes he said 
as for the berkeley scientists theory buckle said it makes 
sense that where the thighbone connects to the shinbone so to 
speak youre going to have problems i would say that theory 
probably is a good one 
in another development clayton giroux the designer of the 
collapsed i880 said he watched in horror as televised newscasts 
showed the wreckage of what he had viewed as one of his greatest 
engineering achievements 
giroux 63 added but he added i dont have guilt over it 
just a strong sense of disappointment and tragedy 
out of this will come learning similar to sylmar the 1971 
earthquake in southern california and future lives will be 
saved giroux said unfortunately we only learn about 
earthquakes from earthquakes 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

