for several decades the national association of 
investors corp has preached a conservative investment philosophy 
through its member clubs and in manuals and a monthly magazine 
smart amateur investors it advised should be able on average 
to double their money in five or six years in sound common stocks 
and do so without taking unusual risks or relying on costly 
professional services 
stories are inspiring but money talks asked what new service 
the naic might offer members it responded a common stock mutual 
