<TEXT>
delta air lines inc said thursday that it and 
singapore airlines will make significant investments in each other 
as part of agreements designed to promote and enhance cooperation 
between the two carriers 
atlantabased delta said in a statement that the agreements 
signed thursday include a 10year marketing pact and two equity 
crosspurchase accords 
ronald w allen deltas chairman and chief executive officer 
said singapore airlines worldwide route system centered in the 
pacific and southeast asia will strongly complement our own 
domestic and emerging international operations 
delta said the marketing agreement involves cooperation in 
schedule coordination codesharing blocked space purchase 
arrangements and possible joint service on certain routes 
code sharing refers to a computer system under which a passenger 
may purchase a single ticket for a route that involves flights on 
both carriers 
under the other accords delta said singapore airlines has 
agreed to buy 25 million shares of delta common stock at a price 
equal to 110 percent of the average closing price of delta shares 
for the two days before and after the agreement was signed and 
delta has agreed to buy the same dollar amount of singapore shares 
based on a similar formula 
allen said the agreements are similar to an arrangement reached 
earlier this year with swissair 
delta said the two carriers have agreed to certain limitations 
on their ability to transfer the shares they are buying and on 
future purchases of their stock 
delta said each carrier also has agreed to vote its shares in 
the same proportion as other shares are voted or as recommended by 
the other airlines board of directors 
the agreements are subject to the approval of singapore 
airlines shareholders 
delta also announced thursday that its board has authorized the 
periodic repurchase of up to 25 million shares of outstanding 
common stock 
</TEXT>
